his shield like the black rock
the first rays of the morning star , swift as the flying deer , strong as a young oak , fierce as an evening wolf , drew his sword
the first rays of the morning star , swift as the flying deer , strong as a young oak , fierce as an evening wolf , drew his sword
glittering like the blue vapours in the valley of Horso
the strong oaks of the forest
the race as the minutes of impatience
of hail at the approach of the sun
thy garments be stained in blood
arise from the mossy bank of the falling waters
thy flowing hair be hid in a helmet
the black companies of the enemy
the roaring waves of the sea
the murmuring voice of the Severn , swelled with rain
a blazing star the sword of Kenrick shone among the Britons
the red lightning of heaven he burned up the ranks of his enemy
Eldulph was a flaming vapour , destruction
like a rock before the sword of Mervin
the branches of the oak beneath their feet
